claim.claim-text:
1) An Internet marketing method, comprising the steps of: 
a) providing an Internet web site with a link to a game screen, the game screen including: 
i) a displayed game image or images made up of a large number of pixels; 
ii) instructions to select a pixel or image area on the game image whose pixel or image area location is then compared against winning pixel or image area location(s) stored in memory; 
iii) one or more ad spaces; 

b) linking the user to a winning response page upon completion of the pixel or image area location comparison if the selected pixel or image area location matches one of the winning pixel or image area locations, or, alternatively; and 
c) linking the user to a losing response page upon completion of the pixel or image area location comparison if the selected pixel or image area location does not match one of the winning pixel or image area locations.

7) An Internet marketing method, comprising the steps of: 
a) providing an Internet web site with a link to a game screen, the game screen including: 
i) a displayed game image made up of a large number of pixels; 
ii) instructions explaining the game rules to a user, the rules including instructions to select a pixel or image area location on the game image whose pixel or image area location is then compared against winning pixel or image area location(s) stored in memory; 
iii) one or more ad spaces including links to other web sites; 

b) linking the user to a winning response page upon completion of the pixel or image area location comparison if the selected pixel or image area location matches one of the winning pixel or image area locations, or, alternatively; 
c) linking the user to a losing response page upon completion of the pixel or image area location comparison if the selected pixel or image area location does not match one of the winning pixel or image area locations; and 
d) displaying one or more ad spaces with each said response page.

11) An Internet marketing game hosted on a host server, said game comprising: 
a) a web site which directs users to a game page to play the game; 
b) said game page including: 
i) a game image made up of a large number of pixels; 
ii) instructions for playing the game pertaining to selecting a pixel or image area location from the game image; 
iii) at least one ad space; 

c) a plurality of losing response pages stored in memory at said host and/or dynamically generated by said host; 
d) at least one winning response page stored in memory at said host and/or dynamically generated by said host; wherein 
e) the server is programmed to: 
i) compare the player's selected pixel or image area location with one or more winning pixel or image area locations stored in memory at said host; 
ii) to display one of said losing response pages to a player when the player's selected pixel or image area location does not match one of the winning pixel or image area locations; and 
iii) to display one of said winning response pages to a player when the player's selected pixel or image area location does match one of the winning pixel or image area locations.
